Basic.desc: Basic test vectors use the simplest possible inputs. These inputs often overlap with inputs from standards and RFCs. One goal of such test vectors is to simply detect distinct algorithms.

MissingNull.desc: The ASN.1 encoding of the digest algorithm lacks a NULL. Such signatures are sometimes accepted for legacy reasons.

ModifiedAsn.desc: The signature contains a modified padding. Accepting signatures with incorrect padding can lead to signature forgery.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

SpecialHash.desc: The signature contains a message with an edge case hash value.

SpecialKey.desc: The signature uses an edge case key. The purpose of this key is to check for arithmetic errors during the verification of the signature.
